data.title: Algorius Net Viewer version 11.8.6 by Algorius Software
data.meta_description: How to uninstall Algorius Net Viewer Version 11.8.6 by Algorius Software? Learn how to remove Algorius Net Viewer Version 11.8.6 from your computer.
data.text:
Algorius Net Viewer

A way to uninstall Algorius Net Viewer from your PC

This web page contains thorough information on how to remove Algorius Net Viewer for Windows. It was coded for Windows by Algorius Software. Further information on Algorius Software can be seen here. You can get more details about Algorius Net Viewer at https://algorius.com. The program is usually located in the C:\Program Files\Algorius\NetViewer folder (same installation drive as Windows). You can remove Algorius Net Viewer by clicking on the Start menu of Windows and pasting the command line MsiExec.exe /I{AB6610F9-1822-4B6C-9454-976463455133}. Note that you might receive a notification for admin rights. Algorius Net Viewer's main file takes around 2.87 MB (3010560 bytes) and its name is NetViewer.exe.

The following executables are installed along with Algorius Net Viewer. They take about 6.30 MB (6611152 bytes) on disk.

InventoryAgent.exe (133.85 KB)

NetViewer.exe (2.87 MB)

NetViewerServer.exe (1.56 MB)

NetViewerServerSetup.exe (1.72 MB)

wol.exe (30.85 KB)
